# Vocabulary: Street Ordering (Northern Mexico)

Me da...
  Give me... (casual but polite — how most people actually order)
  [meh dah]

Échame unos tacos
  Hit me with some tacos
  [EH-chah-meh OO-nohs TAH-kohs]

Con todo
  With everything (on tacos, tortas, etc.)
  [kohn TOH-doh]

Pa' llevar
  To go (shortened 'para llevar')
  [pah yeh-BAHR]

¿Cuánto va a ser?
  How much is it gonna be?
  [KWAHN-toh bah ah sehr]

¿Cuánto te debo?
  How much do I owe you?
  [KWAHN-toh teh DEH-boh]

¡Provecho!
  Enjoy! (shortened 'buen provecho')
  [proh-BEH-choh]

La cuentita
  The check (diminutive — sounds friendlier)
  [lah kwehn-TEE-tah]

# Phrases: Ordering & Requests

Una mesa para dos, por favor
  A table for two, please
  [OO-nah MEH-sah PAH-rah dohs]

Quisiera...
  I would like...
  [kee-see-EH-rah]
  > Quisiera el pollo, por favor.

¿Qué recomienda?
  What do you recommend?
  [keh reh-koh-mee-EHN-dah]

Para mí...
  For me...
  [PAH-rah mee]

La cuenta, por favor
  The check, please
  [lah KWEHN-tah pohr fah-BOHR]

¡Estuvo delicioso!
  It was delicious!
  [ehs-TOO-boh deh-lee-see-OH-soh]

